messageBody:
Nic,

Quite sorry for the delayed response. If you look at
https://github.com/junit-team/junit/tags, you want r4.10. A quick glance
through Google or the github docs should give you the commands you need to
pull down the version-specific source.

If you have any questions in the future, the community at
junit@yahoogroups.com (cc'ed) is often swifter than me individually. Good
luck,

David Saff


On Sun, Feb 24, 2013 at 12:45 PM, Nic Pantieras <eqtp@...> wrote:

> Hello David,
>
> Please forgive me for contacting you directly. I searched github and the
> junit project to determine if there was a way that I could pull down the
> source code for the release version of junit 4.10; basically, a
> get-by-label operation, so that I could step through it while debugging.
>
> Is this possible from github? Am I on the wrong track?
>
> Thank you, and again, sorry for contacting you directly.
>
> Cheers,
> Nic
